Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity

Binary search on m × n elements:

O(log(m * n))
Space Complexity
O(1)
Pattern Recognition

Use this approach when:

Every row is sorted.
The first element of a row is greater than the last element of the previous row.

This means the matrix can be treated as a single sorted array.

Important Conversion Formula
row = mid / cols;
col = mid % cols;
Core Idea
